+# Word Garden
+
+Word Garden is a friendly terminal word-guessing game. Guess the hidden word before the garden runs out of water. It is like Hangman, but with plants instead of gallows.
+
+Word Garden is a small TUI game designed as a more cheerful alternative to Hangman. It is intended as a slightly more adventurous "Hello World" project for testing AI-assisted software development. The game includes input validation, state management, a simple loop, win/loss conditions, and a friendly terminal interface.
+
+## Installation
+
+No external dependencies — Word Garden uses only Python 3.11+ standard library.
+
+```bash
+# Clone or download the repository
+cd word_garden
+```
+
+## How to Play
+
+```bash
+python3 -m word_garden
+```
+
+This starts a game on normal difficulty (6 water, words with 5–8 letters).
+
+### Command-line Options
+
+**`--difficulty`** — Choose game difficulty:
+- `easy`: 8 water, 4–6 letter words (default: normal)
+- `normal`: 6 water, 5–8 letter words
+- `hard`: 4 water, 7+ letter words
+
+Example:
+```bash
+python3 -m word_garden --difficulty easy
+python3 -m word_garden --difficulty hard
+```
+
+**`--ascii`** — Use ASCII-only output (no emoji) for terminals that don't render emoji:
+```bash
+python3 -m word_garden --ascii
+```
+
+## Rules
+
+1. **Guess letters** — Press one letter at a time to guess. Lowercase and uppercase both work.
+2. **Correct guesses** help the garden grow and reveal letters in the word.
+3. **Incorrect guesses** use up one unit of water and cause a weed to appear.
+4. **Win** by revealing the entire word before running out of water.
+5. **Lose** when water reaches zero before the word is complete.
+6. **Invalid input** (multiple letters, non-alphabetic, empty) does not consume water — just re-enter.
+
+## Sample Screen
+
+```text
+🌱 Word Garden
+
+Word:     G _ R _ E _
+Guessed:  A E G R
+Water:    4/6 💧💧💧💧
+Weeds:    2 🌿🌿
+
+Good guess! The garden grows.
+
+Guess a letter: _
+```
+
+## Exit
+
+Press **Ctrl-D** (EOF) or **Ctrl-C** (KeyboardInterrupt) to quit at any time. The game will say goodbye and exit cleanly.
+
+## Testing
+
+Run the test suite:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest discover -s tests
+```
+
+This runs over 80 engine tests plus comprehensive UI and main loop tests.
+
+## Project Structure
+
+- **`word_garden/game.py`** — Core game logic (engine contract, no I/O).
+- **`word_garden/words.py`** — Word list and difficulty selection.
+- **`word_garden/ui.py`** — Terminal rendering (no I/O).
+- **`word_garden/main.py`** — Main loop and entry point.
+- **`word_garden/__main__.py`** — Package entry point (`python3 -m word_garden`).
+- **`tests/test_game.py`** — Engine tests.
+- **`tests/test_words.py`** — Word selection tests.
+- **`tests/test_ui.py`** — UI and main loop tests.
+
+## Design Principles
+
+Word Garden stays small, readable, and pleasant. It separates concerns:
+
+- **game.py** handles state and logic (no I/O, no randomness unless injected).
+- **words.py** manages the word list and difficulty parameters.
+- **ui.py** renders the display (pure functions, no I/O).
+- **main.py** orchestrates the loop and handles user input/output.
+
+This design makes the game easy to test, extend, and adapt.
+
+---
+
+Enjoy the game!
